      • findServiceBySymbol

        public IMarketDataService findServiceBySymbol(List services,
                                              IFIXMessage message,
                                              String symbol)
        The search logic is: If there is only one service configured, try and use that. If securityLocator tag is not null, use it to identify the service. If still not found, search for existing symbol on all services. Return service if symbol is only found on that service. Return null if symbol is not found on any service or if it is found on more than one service.
        Specified by:
        findServiceBySymbol in interface IServiceLocator
        Parameters:
        services - List of market data services.
        message - MarketDataRequest or SecurityStatusRequest message.
        symbol - symbol
        Returns:
        null if service can not be located or market data service to handle this message and symbol.

      • findServiceByLocatorTag

        public IMarketDataService findServiceByLocatorTag(List services,
                                                  IFIXMessage message)
        Find a market data service by tag.

        Note that market data services need not have an locator tag set so this search may find nothing. That is, only an exact match results in anything being returned. The caller must explicitly handle this.

        Specified by:
        findServiceByLocatorTag in interface IServiceLocator
        Parameters:
        services - List of market data services.
        message - request message.
        Returns:
        The market data service with a locatorTag exactly matching the message locator tag value, null if no such market data service is found.
